mulan.experiments

Class ENTCS13FeatureSelection

  • java.lang.Object
    • mulan.experiments.ENTCS13FeatureSelection

  • public class ENTCS13FeatureSelection
extends Object

    Class replicating the experiment in Newton Spolaôr, Everton Alvares Cherman, Maria Carolina Monard, and Huei Diana Lee. 2013. A Comparison of Multi-label Feature Selection Methods using the Problem Transformation Approach. Electron. Notes Theor. Comput. Sci. 292 (March 2013), 135-151.

    Version:
    2013.07.25
    Author:
    Newton Spolaôr (newtonspolaor@gmail.com)

    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
        Main class. This command requires the specification of two filenames and the feature selection method name as command-line arguments. These arguments correspond respectively to the name of the XML and the ARFF files specifying the actual dataset, according to the Mulan standard (http://mulan.sourceforge.net/format.html), and the name of the feature selection method to be used. The methods currently available are named "RF-BR", "RF-LP", "IG-BR" and "IG-LP".
        Parameters:
        args - command line arguments

      • buildMultiLabelFeatureSelection

        public static ASEvaluation buildMultiLabelFeatureSelection(String multiLabelFeatureSelectionMethod,
                                                           MultiLabelInstances dataSet)
        Initiates ASEvaluation given by a Weka feature importance measure and a Mulan approach to deal with MultiLabelInstances
        Parameters:
        multiLabelFeatureSelectionMethod - name of the multi-label feature selection method ("RF-BR", "RF-LP", "IG-BR", "IG-LP)
        dataSet - original dataset with all features. This dataset should not have any feature/label named "class"
        Returns:
        an initialized ASEvaluation to perform multi-label feature selection

        public static double[][] sortedEvaluatedAttributeList(int[] featureIndices,
                                                      AttributeEvaluator attributeEval)
        Given an array with feature indices, this method returns a double matrix similar to the one returned by the method rankedAttributes from the Weka Ranker class
        Parameters:
        featureIndices - an array of feature indices
        attributeEval - the attribute evaluator to guide the evaluation
        Returns:
        a matrix of sorted attribute indices and evaluations
